        <!-- The Problem -->
        <section id="problem" class="section">
            <h2>The Problem</h2>
            <div class="problem-box">
                <p><strong>Montefiore Square currently functions as a pass-through, not a destination.</strong> Despite its prime location and high foot traffic, the plaza suffers from critical deficiencies that undermine its potential as a community asset.</p>
            </div>
            <ul class="analysis-list">
                <li><i class="fas fa-shield-alt"></i> <strong>Safety Issues:</strong> Poor nighttime lighting, unclear pedestrian crossings, and obstructed sightlines create hazardous conditions.</li>
                <li><i class="fas fa-tree"></i> <strong>Comfort Deficits:</strong> Only 3 benches for a high-traffic area; zero shade structures; 85% impervious surface creates heat island effect.</li>
                <li><i class="fas fa-store"></i> <strong>Economic Missed Opportunity:</strong> Nearby businesses report minimal spillover activity — the plaza actively discourages lingering.</li>
                <li><i class="fas fa-paintbrush"></i> <strong>Identity Void:</strong> No reflection of Harlem's rich cultural legacy, no public art, no community programming infrastructure.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- Site / Context -->
        <section id="context" class="section">
            <h2>Site Understanding</h2>
            <p>Montefiore Square sits at the intersection of Broadway and West 167th Street, connecting residential blocks to commercial corridors. Site analysis reveals critical patterns that inform the redesign.</p>
            <div class="grid-2 mt-3">
                <div class="thumbnail-card">
                    <div class="thumbnail-img">
                        <img src="images/movement-analysis.jpg" alt="Movement Patterns Analysis">
                    </div>
                    <div class="thumbnail-caption">
                        <h4>Movement Patterns</h4>
                        <p>Desire paths cut diagonally across barren concrete; no clear pedestrian-vehicle hierarchy creates friction points at plaza edges.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="thumbnail-card">
                    <div class="thumbnail-img">
                        <img src="images/business-map.jpg" alt="Business Activity Map">
                    </div>
                    <div class="thumbnail-caption">
                        <h4>Business Ecosystem</h4>
                        <p>Adjacent bodegas, restaurants, and barbershops have no outdoor extension opportunities — the plaza fails to activate the local economy.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="thumbnail-card">
                    <div class="thumbnail-img">
                        <img src="images/comfort-study.jpg" alt="Comfort & Microclimate Study">
                    </div>
                    <div class="thumbnail-caption">
                        <h4>Comfort & Microclimate</h4>
                        <p>Summer surface temperatures exceed 120°F due to lack of vegetation; winter winds channel through unbroken hardscape.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="thumbnail-card">
                    <div class="thumbnail-img">
                        <img src="images/community-needs.jpg" alt="Community Needs Assessment">
                    </div>
                    <div class="thumbnail-caption">
                        <h4>Community Needs</h4>
                        <p>Local residents express desire for gathering spaces, weekend markets, and programming that celebrates Harlem's identity.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Design Options (AI-Generated) -->
        <section id="design" class="section">
            <h2>AI-Assisted Design Exploration <span class="ai-badge">DALL·E</span></h2>
            <p>Using site photographs from Montefiore Square as visual references, I prompted DALL·E to generate three distinct redesign directions. Each option was iterated multiple times to refine materials, planting schemes, and programmatic elements.</p>
            
            <div class="grid mt-3">
                <div class="thumbnail-card">
                    <div class="thumbnail-img">
                        <img src="images/option-a.jpg" alt="Market Plaza Design Option">
                    </div>
                    <div class="thumbnail-caption">
                        <h4>Option A: Market Plaza</h4>
                        <p>Modular kiosks, weekend farmer's market layout, vibrant tensile shades.</p>
                        <p class="text-muted"><small><strong>Prompt:</strong> "redesign this plaza as a community market plaza with kiosks, vendor zones, public art, and weekend programming, Harlem Renaissance inspired colors"</small></p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="thumbnail-card">
                    <div class="thumbnail-img">
                        <img src="images/option-b.jpg" alt="Green Wellness Design Option">
                    </div>
                    <div class="thumbnail-caption">
                        <h4>Option B: Green Wellness</h4>
                        <p>Rain gardens, pollinator plants, wooden deck seating, yoga lawn.</p>
                        <p class="text-muted"><small><strong>Prompt:</strong> "redesign this plaza as a green wellness plaza with shade trees, seasonal planting, flexible seating, and bioswales"</small></p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="thumbnail-card">
                    <div class="thumbnail-img">
                        <img src="images/option-c.jpg" alt="Cultural Pulse Design Option">
                    </div>
                    <div class="thumbnail-caption">
                        <h4>Option C: Cultural Pulse <span class="ai-badge">Selected</span></h4>
                        <p>Integrated stage, light art installations, café terraces, community board.</p>
                        <p class="text-muted"><small><strong>Prompt:</strong> "transform this existing hardscape plaza into a lively Harlem-inspired community-centered public space with jazz-age aesthetics, interactive lighting, and flexible performance zones"</small></p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="info-box mt-3">
                <p><strong><i class="fas fa-robot"></i> Prompt Iteration Log:</strong> Initial prompts were too generic. After incorporating site-specific context ("Montefiore Square," "Harlem," "Broadway") and using actual site screenshots as visual references, the AI generated more contextual layouts. The <strong>Cultural Pulse</strong> option was selected for its balance of cultural identity, economic activation potential, and flexible programming capacity.</p>
            </div>
