        <!-- Reflection / Conclusion -->
        <section id="reflection" class="section">
            <h2>Human Reflection on AI Use</h2>
            <div class="grid-2">
                <div class="reflection-card">
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-microchip"></i> What AI Helped With</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Generating high-fidelity visualizations of diverse design directions in seconds</li>
                        <li>Iterating color palettes and materiality reflecting Harlem's aesthetic</li>
                        <li>Suggesting unconventional seating layouts (stoop concept) from cultural prompts</li>
                        <li>Rapid prototyping of before/after comparisons for stakeholder communication</li>
                        <li>Exploring material combinations and planting schemes efficiently</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="reflection-card">
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-brain"></i> What Required Human Judgment</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Selecting final proposal based on real-world site constraints (DOT regulations, bus stop adjacencies)</li>
                        <li>Validating AI-generated layouts against NYC Street Design Manual accessibility standards</li>
                        <li>Defining the essential question and ensuring academic rigor beyond visual appeal</li>
                        <li>Grounding design in community business needs — AI suggested generic "cafes," human insight identified bodega and barbershop integration</li>
                        <li>Ensuring cultural authenticity and sensitivity to Harlem's heritage</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="quote-box mt-3">
                <p><i class="fas fa-quote-left"></i> AI served as a rapid ideation partner, enabling exploration of multiple design directions quickly. However, the final design is anchored in site-specific analysis, cultural sensitivity, and the project track's focus on business activation. The prompts were refined using actual Montefiore Square screenshots to ensure spatial accuracy and contextual relevance.</p>
            </div>

